  "body": "**Ampersands in query params within src/href attributes are being escaped**\n\nCurrently, all attributes are sanitized for the browser using [`escapeTextContentForBrowser`](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/67f8524e88abbf1ac0fd86d38a0477d11fbc7b3e/src/renderers/dom/shared/escapeTextContentForBrowser.js). However, in the case of `src` or `href` attributes, this will escape `&` within query parameters.\n\n**Example**\n\n``` js\nReactDOMServer.renderToStaticMarkup(<a href=\"http://foo.com?a=1&b=2\" />);\n// => <a href=\"http://foo.com?a=1&amp;b=2\"></a>\n```\n\nThe attribute name is available until calling [quoteAttributeValueForBrowser](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/74cce27fe049bbb677c7158de0f3daed5e013fde/src/renderers/dom/shared/DOMPropertyOperations.js#L106). There would need to a be a degree of refactor to create conditional behavior, with consideration given to attributes that might contain urls.\n\n**Possible attributes to alter**\n- `src`\n- `href`\n- `data-` variations of the above\n\nI don't know if this is a bug or if it exists by design, for non-obvious reasons.\n\nVersions `0.14.x`, `15.x`\n",
